      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $a,m,n\\ \\in \\N^{*}$, $a\\ge 2$, et $d = (a^n - 1) \\wedge (a^m - 1)$.",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(a,m,n\\ \\in \\N^{*}\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(a\\ge 2\\)</span>, et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(d\n= (a^n - 1) \\wedge (a^m - 1)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "895fea35-dcc3-4921-b180-956df5afdf80",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $n = qm + r$ la division euclidienne de $n$ par $m$.\n      D{\\'e}montrer que $a^n \\equiv a^r (\\mathrm{mod}\\, {a^m - 1})$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n = qm + r\\)</span> la division\neuclidienne de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> par <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(m\\)</span>. D<span>é</span>montrer que <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(a^n \\equiv a^r (\\mathrm{mod}\\, {a^m -\n1})\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "8b187140-f4bb-44b5-9dcd-31e09a88b132",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$a^m - 1\\mid (a^{qm} - 1)a^r = a^n - a^r$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(a^m - 1\\mid (a^{qm} - 1)a^r = a^n -\na^r\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "649fbe5e-0fdf-455b-98ab-606c2b8da563",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "En d{\\'e}duire que $d = (a^r - 1) \\wedge (a^m - 1)$,\n      puis $d = a^{(n \\wedge m)} - 1$.",
        "html": "<p>En d<span>é</span>duire que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(d = (a^r - 1)\n\\wedge (a^m - 1)\\)</span>, puis <span class=\"math inline\">\\(d = a^{(n\n\\wedge m)} - 1\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
